{{Infobox Person |name = Jean Riachi |birth_date = 1963 |occupation = CEO of FFA Private Bank |alma mater = HEC Paris/INSEAD |image=Jean Riachi.jpg}}
'''Jean Riachi''' (born in 1963) is the founder and current [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] and Chairman of the Board of [[FFA Private Bank]], Lebanon's largest [[investment bank]].<ref> [http://us.ft.com/ftgateway/superpage.ft?news_id=fto102020081402177358 Financial Times]{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He founded the company in 1994 as a regulated [[Financial institution]]. In 2007, the Company was granted a banking license,<ref> [http://www.zawya.com/story.cfm/sidZAWYA20070807134605 Zawya]</ref> Jean Riachi is also the Chairman of FFA Dubai, the first Lebanese Financial Institution to get a license from the DFSA in the Dubai International Financial Center (DIFC).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.gulfnews.com/articles/06/11/03/10079535.html |title=Gulf News |access-date=2008-10-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081012150601/http://www.gulfnews.com/articles/06/11/03/10079535.html |archive-date=2008-10-12 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
==Education== Born an raised in Lebanon, Jean Riachi completed his high school education at [[Lycee Louis-le-Grand]] in Paris and graduated from [[HEC Paris]] business school in 1985 with an MSc in management. He also holds a Certificate in Corporate Governance (IDP-C) from [[INSEAD]]'s International Directors Program.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.associationhec.com/revue/revue302/article1.php |title=Association HEC |access-date=2008-10-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707180456/http://www.associationhec.com/revue/revue302/article1.php |archive-date=2011-07-07 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> <ref>[https://centres.insead.edu/corporate-governance/ INSEAD]</ref>
==Other== Jean Riachi was a member of the MInistry of FInance's Committee in charge of drafting the new Lebanese Financial Markets Law.<ref>[http://www.oecd.org/dataoecd/23/8/38472929.pdf OECD]</ref><ref>[http://www.atypon-link.com/OXF/doi/pdf/10.5555/erlb.2005.2.Emerging_Lebanon_2005.65?cookieSet=1 Oxford Business Group]{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He is also member of Human RIghts Watch's Beirut Committee (HRW),<ref>[https://www.hrw.org Human Rights Watch]</ref> board member of the Lebanese American Chamber of Commerce (AMCHAM Lebanon).<ref>[https://www.amcham.org.lb/template.asp?id=3 American Chamber Of Commerce - Lebanon]</ref> and President of the Faraya Ski Club<ref>[http://www.lebskifed.com/services.asp?ttl=Clubs Faraya Sporting Club]</ref>
